    "The regulatory intervention should be proportionate to the hazards net of safeguards.",
    "Risk tolerance thresholds-in the AIA, the risk categories-indicate which risks are accepted without (strong) precautions and which instead require (further) mitigation practices.",
    "In the AIA, the benchmark to calculate the risk of AIs is their potential adverse impact on health, safety, and EU fundamental rights.",
    "As a result, the AIA classifies AIs according to four risk categories: unacceptable, high, limited, and minimal (Kaplan & Garrick, 1981).",
    "8 Stricter requirements are prescribed for suppliers and users of riskier AIs."
